name: A Cappella Council
description_preview: Council of a cappella groups on campus.

name: Active Minds at the University of Chicago
description_preview: The national purpose of Active Minds is to empower university students to speak openly about mental health in order to educate others and encourage help-seeking behavior.

name: African and Caribbean Students Association
description_preview: Celebrating the rich cultures of Africa and the Caribbean on campus.

name: AI @ UChicago
description_preview: The purpose of this organization shall be to educate members on the ethics, use cases, and inner workings of AI. Furthermore, this RSO will seek to kindle a community surrounding the broad topic of AI.

name: Aikido Kokikai
description_preview: Kokikai Aikido is a self-defense art that uses throws, pins, and an opponent's momentum to defend against striking and grabbing attacks.  For maximum effect, students learn how to relax properly and develop good posture and balance.

name: Allied Scholars for Animal Protection UChicago
description_preview: UChicago Allied Scholars for Animal Protection provides a unified infrastructure for sustainable and effective animal advocacy on college campuses, including ongoing logistical support, funding, educational programming, and career mentorships.

name: Alpha Kappa Psi (Beta Epsilon)
description_preview: Alpha Kappa Psi is America's oldest, largest, and most successful professional business fraternity.

name: Alpha Phi Omega
description_preview:
Alpha Phi Omega is a national co-ed community service fraternity. Our cardinal principles are leadership, friendship, and service. We participate in social and service events throughout the city. 
If you need volunteers, email uchi.apo.service@gmail.com

name: American Constitution Society
description_preview: The American Constitution Society is an organization of progressive law students, professors, and legal professionals. ACS works to uphold the Constitution by ensuring that the law is a force for protecting our democracy and the public interest.

name: American Lung Cancer Screening Initiative
description_preview: Do you want to gain patient exposure and clinical hours talking to individuals about lung cancer screening? ALCSI strives to increase lung cancer screening awareness. Interested in making tangible impact and saving lives? Email rico1604@uchicago.edu

name: American Medical Student Association
description_preview:
Organization purpose: 
1)Improving quality of health care in the US and worldwide, 2) Acting as a resource for social and moral interests in medical education, and 3) Protecting the interests of medical students and residents

name: American Red Cross of University of Chicago
description_preview: The American Red Cross of University of Chicago (ARCUC) is a collegiate club of the American Red Cross of Greater Chicago (ARCGC) chapter. We seek to take a strong leadership role in recruiting support for the Red Cross and our surrounding communities.

name: Animal Legal Defense Fund - The University of Chicago Law School
description_preview: ALDF is dedicated to providing a forum for education, advocacy, and scholarship aimed at protecting the lives and advancing the interests of animals through the legal system.

name: Ankara Magic
description_preview: Afrobeats Dance Team

name: Anthropology Students Association
description_preview: The University of Chicago Anthropology Students Association was set up to promote anthropology and anthropology-related research and events at the University of Chicago. The association is open to all members of the University of Chicago community.

name: Apsara
description_preview: Apsara is UChicago's premier classical Indian dance company. We produce full-length shows in the winter and spring, and participate in the annual SASA (South Asian Students Association) show. We welcome dancers of all backgrounds and levels!

name: Arab Student Association
description_preview: We aim to cultivate an active community for Arab students and students interested in Arab culture, heritage, and identity at the University of Chicago and to support the community with a range of professional development opportunities.

name: Archery
description_preview:
The University of Chicago Archery Club's main goal is to promote the sport of archery at both a competitive and a non-competitive level.

For more information, please email us at ArcheryBoard@lists.uchicago.edu

The Argentine Tango Club promotes Argentine Tango on the University of Chicago campus. We organize Argentine Tango classes, dance parties and events showcasing Argentine Tango in literature, figurative arts, Argentine traditions and music history.

name: Armenian Students Association
description_preview: The Armenian Students' Association is a group of students interested in the Armenian language, culture, and greater nation. We aim to explore Armenian identity within the University at large, through our storied history, culture, politics, and traditions

name: Army Reserve Officer Training Corps
description_preview: The mission of Army ROTC at the University of Chicago is to provide Students who are interested in leadership development, physical training, and basic Army doctrine an opportunity to participate in ROTC activities without incurring any obligation.

name: ArtShould
description_preview: ArtShould is an arts community service RSO that aims to promote art on the University of Chicago campus and in the Hyde Park community. We mentor youths in Chicago Public Schools through after-school art programs and host creative events on campus.

name: Asian American InterVarsity
description_preview: Following Jesus, Living His Kingdom, Renewing our Campus

name: Asian Pacific American Medical Students Association
description_preview: The University of Chicago Asian Pacific American Medical Students Association (APAMSA) seeks to promote health and wellness for all Asian and Pacific Islander communities and to encourage University of Chicago students to serve these patient populations.

name: Asian Policy Forum
description_preview: APF connects students with various leaders and experts of Asia-related policies to inspire conversations on Asian issues, and enhance diversity and inclusion through organizing cultural events. With us, you will grasp the dynamics of Asia and policies.

name: Association for Women in Mathematics
description_preview: We support women in mathematics.

name: Badminton
description_preview: The UC Badminton Club provides a forum for members to play recreational badminton regularly at the university, as well as occasional opportunities for competitive badminton at tournaments and matches with nearby schools.

name: Baha'i Association of the University of Chicago
description_preview: The goal of the Baha'i Association is to create a forum for discussion and action based on the writings and teachings of the Baha'i Faith and interfaith dialogue with other world Faiths.

name: Ballroom and Latin Dance Association
description_preview: BLDA is dedicated to promoting the awareness and appreciation of Ballroom and Social Latin dance on campus by providing dance lessons and social dance events for both UChicago and the city of Chicago. We are home to UChicago's Competitive Ballroom Team.

name: Bite Culinary Magazine
description_preview: A quarterly print culinary magazine and online blog for those interested in food-writing and photography, including features, recipes, and reviews.

name: Black Action in Public Policy Studies
description_preview: Black Action in Public Policy Studies (BAPPS), is committed to cultivating an inclusive community for our members. Through our programming, we center the experiences and needs of Black people when delving into issues of inequality within public policy.

name: Black Law Students Association
description_preview: The purpose of this organization is to articulate, promote, and discuss issues of concern to Black law students and to facilitate the interaction between Black law students, current members and alumni of the Law School and the Chicago community.

name: Black Student Fellowship
description_preview: Spring 2024 New RSO

name: BlackGen Capital
description_preview: Spring 2024 New RSO

name: Blacklight Magazine
description_preview: Blacklight Magazine is a collective of young creatives and a platform for marginalized voices. We create visual and literary art. We transform. We disrupt tradition.

name: Blockchain Chicago
description_preview: Blockchain Chicago aims to unite the university communities growing around blockchain technology by promoting and constructing quality, multidisciplinary, educational experiences for curious and inquisitive souls.

name: Blue Chips
description_preview: Founded in 2003, The Blue Chips is the University of Chicago’s premier investment club. As a group of over 50 active undergraduate members, we manage a $170,000 fundamental value-focused equity portfolio, gifted to us by Greg Wendt (A.B. '83).

name: Boxing Club
description_preview: Boxing Club Sport

name: Brazilian Student Association
description_preview: The Brazilian Student Association (BSA) is committed to bringing the Brazilian culture to the University of Chicago. We bring the Brazilian community and those interested in Brazil together to share experiences in a variety of events throughout the year.

name: Bridge Club
description_preview:
We are a social club that plays bridge every week during the school term. We also play in several tournaments per year.

Our meetings are Thursdays from 8-11pm; stay as long as you want. We're happy to teach beginners.

name: Bridge to College
description_preview: The purpose of Bridge to College is to help underserved Chicago Public School high school students develop a stronger working knowledge of what college and the application process entails through College Days and our one-on-one mentorship program.

name: Bridgeport Free Clinic
description_preview: The mission of the Bridgeport Free Clinic (BFC) is to provide drop-in medical care for the uninsured community of Bridgeport.

name: Business Organization for Latino Development
description_preview: BOLD is the premier community for Latino business professionals at UChicago

name: Cadenza
description_preview: A high voice a cappella group serenading UChicago since 1989, previously named "Unaccompanied Women."

name: Campus Catalyst
description_preview: campusCATALYST is a student-run organization at the University of Chicago that engages in high-impact pro bono consulting with local Chicago non-profits.

name: Cana
description_preview: Cana is a student-run Christian journal that publishes creative content exploring faith in a university setting. Our mission is to engage with relevant topics in the space where the "life of the mind" meets a call to discipleship.

name: Catcher in the Rhyme
description_preview: Catcher in the Rhyme is a student-run organization to encourage self-expression through spoken word poetry both on campus and off.

name: Catholic Students Association
description_preview: This is a group dedicated to developing Catholic community in the student population of the University of Chicago through various social, service, and spiritual activities.

name: Catholic Students Association for Graduate and Professional Students
description_preview: We aim to foster a community of Catholic graduate students, professional students, friends, and interested parties of any religious belief, through spiritual, social and service events.

name: Center for Leadership and Involvement
description_preview: The Center for Leadership and Involvement supports the goals of the University of Chicago by creating meaningful involvement opportunities and fostering inclusive environments which advance student learning.

name: Central Asian Studies Society
description_preview: The Central Asian Studies Society promotes the study of and engagement with the histories, languages, and cultures of Central Asia. We define Central Asia broadly, stretching from the Caspian Sea and Afghanistan to Xinjiang and Mongolia.

name: Chabad
description_preview: Chabad provides a friendly and welcoming environment for everyone on campus to celebrate Jewish festivities, expand their knowledge of Judaism, pray, and meet new friends.

name: Charles River Economics Labs
description_preview: We are a group of undergraduate researchers at UChicago who conduct pro bono economic policy research for governments, intergovernmental organizations, and policy think tanks. Please contact us if you are interested in this unique opportunity!

name: Cheerleading
description_preview: UC Cheer stunts, dances, cheers, and tumbles to pump up school spirit, not just at basketball and football games, but all over the school. Check out our Facebook and Instagram pages for updates on workshops, tryouts, games, and events!

name: Chemistry Society (Benzene)
description_preview: Benzene is a chemistry interest club for undergraduate and graduate students.

name: Chess Club
description_preview: Chess club provides an open and casual environment where anyone can play anyone on Tuesday nights. We also sponsor our members to compete in tournaments, teach at a local CPS school, and more. No experience level requirement. Join: tinyurl.com/y25h25re

name: Chicago Debate Society
description_preview: The Chicago Debate Society is University of Chicago's competitive parliamentary debate team. CDS competes in the American and British Parliamentary debate circuits while promoting discourse on campus through public debates.

name: Chicago Economics Forum
description_preview: The Chicago Economics Forum aims to bring economics into dialogue with diverse perspectives from peer disciplines, business, and technology to explore contemporary topics from globalization to environmental regulation.

name: Chicago Italian Appreciation Organization
description_preview: This organization aims to promote Italian culture on campus and to provide a forum for students interested in Italian studies in which they can share their ideas. Knowing Italian is not necessary, but a love for the culture is!

name: Chicago Journal of Foreign Policy
description_preview: Student-run undergraduate review, focusing on foreign policy and foreign affairs.

name: Chicago Journal of Sociology
description_preview: The Chicago Journal of Sociology seeks to publish high-quality sociological research papers written by undergraduates, from the University of Chicago and other Chicago-based universities; the Journal publishes an annual volume of edited B.A. theses.
The Chicago Justice Initiative is an organization created to educate University of Chicago students about social justice issues that relate to UChicago students and the broader Chicago community.

name: Chicago Linguistic Society
description_preview: CLS coordinates academic and social events for linguistics department members and affiliates. In addition, the Society organizes a yearly conference, with a history of almost 60 years.

name: Chicago Raas Team
description_preview: Chicago Raas is a competitive dance team at the University of Chicago. Raas is a very energetic and lively Indian folk dance from the state of Gujarat, typically performed in a folk setting.

name: Chicago Shady Dealer
description_preview: The only intentional humor publication of the University of Chicago, the Shady Dealer provides our campus and community with its fair share of satirical news and humorous writing.

name: Chicago Street Medicine
description_preview: Chicago Street Medicine's mission is to improve the health and well-being of people who are experiencing unsheltered homelessness on the South Side of Chicago.

name: Chicago Studies
description_preview: Chicago Studies engages the intellectual, creative, and civic energies of University of Chicago undergraduates in the life of the diverse communities that make up our world-class city.

name: Chicago Swing Dance Society
description_preview: The Chicago Swing Dance Society is dedicated to teaching and promoting swing dancing to all, and regularly organizes free lessons and social dances for the UChicago and wider Chicagoland community. Contact us through our facebook or instagram!

name: China and Beyond
description_preview: China and Beyond aims to create a close academic community to discuss China-related issues and help raise awareness about UChicago in China.

name: Chinese Student Christian Fellowship
description_preview: We welcome Chinese students and scholars at University of Chicago as well as local Chinese to join us for bible study and sharing our experience in Lord, and help them settle down in Hyde Park area.

name: Chinese Students and Scholars Association
description_preview: We are a community for fellow Chinese students and scholars, striving to offer assistance and facilitate communication. At the same time, we serve as a bridge between the Chinese and other communities of the University to promote Chinese culture.

name: Chinese Undergraduate Students Association
description_preview: UChicago CUSA (Chinese Undergraduate Students Association) is one of the University’s largest cultural-interest communities and seeks to spread the richness of Chinese culture across campus through social events, shows, film, and food.

name: Christians on Campus
description_preview: We are a Christian RSO who seeks to help students know Christ and grow in the Christian faith both individually and with one another at UChicago. We hold weekly Bible studies and fellowship with families in the community. Come and join us!

name: Classical Lecture Society
description_preview: Every year the Classical Lecture Society brings two guest speakers to our campus to discuss various topics in the study of the classics.

name: College Bowl Team
description_preview: College Bowl, also known as quiz bowl, is an academic team competition. We compete against other college teams from around the U.S. (and the world) on questions that test knowledge of history, science, literature, arts, and beyond.

name: College Council
description_preview: The undergraduate representative council of Student Government.

name: College Fed Challenge Team
description_preview: Fed Challenge participants research the economy, formulate a monetary policy proposal, and compete against other colleges by presenting/defending their proposal to economists at their regional Federal Reserve Bank.

name: College Republicans
description_preview: The UChicago Republicans represent an array of students who passionately advocate for individual liberty and government accountability while engaging the campus body in political discourse and substantive programming.

name: Colombians at UChicago
description_preview: Colombian students at The University of Chicago

name: Comer Tutors
description_preview: Student tutors that provide academic services at the University of Chicago Comer Children's Hospital with the goal of promoting learning and helping with homework while patients are unable to attend school.

name: Commedia dell'Arte
description_preview: UChicago Commedia is a theatrical ensemble committed to practicing and sharing the art of Commedia dell'Arte. Commedia is a sixteenth-century art form hailing from Italy that marries physical theater, improvisation, mask work, and slapstick.

name: Community Health Initiative
description_preview: To provide for the medical care and overall wellness of the residents of Maria Shelter, a transitional shelter for women and children, in Englewood, and as well as for the patients at the Community Health Clinic in West Town.

name: Council On University Programming
description_preview: The Council on University Programming is a student-run board providing UChicago with large-scale entertainment. We oversee the majority of UChicago traditions, such as Kuvia, Snowball, and Summer Breeze.

name: Crew
description_preview: UChicago Crew competes nationally and internationally in collegiate regattas.  Founded in 1976, we are the largest sports club on campus.  Visit our website or Facebook page to stay updated on our events and races!

name: Cricket Club
description_preview:
Players of all skill levels are welcome to join! 

To get updates, join the facebook group at www.facebook.com/groups/uchicagocricket or the WhatsApp group (DM the president!)

name: Crime & Justice Policy Association
description_preview: CJPA is a hub through which University of Chicago students and the greater Chicago community can educate ourselves and others about issues of crime, public safety, drug policy, violence prevention, and other issues of criminal justice.

name: Critical Understanding of Liturgies and Traditions
description_preview: Spring 2024 New RSO

name: CS Student Activities Council
description_preview: A group to bring together all of UChicago's students interested in tech.

name: Cup of Theater
description_preview: Cup of Theater is a space for students to participate in more experimental and less regulated theater productions and other role-playing entertainment than those of University Theater.

name: Dance Council
description_preview: The University of Chicago Dance Council is a co-curricular program with Theater and Performance Studies involving all existing dance RSOs on campus.

name: Dear Asian Youth
description_preview: The UChicago chapter of Dear Asian Youth seeks to empower APIDA (Asian Pacific Islander Desi American) youth, increase overall awareness about APIDA issues and culture, and promote political engagement and intersectional activism.

Defenders is an organization at the Law School. Our goal is to help students start their legal careers as public defenders. To that end, we host events to connect students with public defenders and highlight issues within the criminal justice system.

name: Delta Sigma Pi Professional Business Fraternity- Alpha Psi Chapter
description_preview: Delta Sigma Pi promotes the study of business in UChicago's theoretical academic environment. We are striving to build a co-ed community based on lifelong professional fulfillment, a lasting commitment to service, and successful personal relationships.

name: Derivatives Group
description_preview: Derivatives Group (Quant) Trading is dedicated to educating its members on the public financial markets, with a focus on financial derivatives, in order to prepare them for academic research and careers in industry.

name: Derivatives of Data Science
description_preview: We explore the myriad applications of data science in economics, mathematics, biology, social sciences, and many more. We host prestigious guest speakers from industry and academia alike, facilitating productive engagement for our members.

name: Dirt Red Brass Band
description_preview: New Orleans-style brass band. Look for us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/pages/UChicagos-Dirt-Red-Brass-Band/393794394033909

name: Documentary Films
description_preview: Doc Films screens new and repertory films every day of the school year and four days a week in the summer. We aim to bring a wide variety of film to campus for the University community as well as the general public.

name: DoGS Lunch
description_preview: This organization provides a venue for constructive interaction amongst students in disciplines within the geophysical sciences and related subjects. Lunch-time meetings provide an audience for graduate student from Geosci to present their research.

name: East African Student Association
description_preview: The East African Student Association aims to bring together East African students on campus in addition to celebrating and sharing a shared background and culture.

name: Eckhart Consulting
description_preview: Since 2002, Eckhart Consulting has advised over 150 of the world's leading corporations, nonprofits, startups, and civic institutions. Collaborating closely with top-tier professionals and executives, EC consultants foster strategic change and creativity

name: Edge Entrepreneurship
description_preview: Edge is the undergraduate organization for entrepreneurship at UChicago.

name: Edmund Burke Society
description_preview: The purpose of the Edmund Burke Society shall be to provide a forum at the University of Chicago for conservative political debate and literary discussion.

name: Emergency Medical Services
description_preview: The University of Chicago Emergency Medical Service (UCEMS) is dedicated to providing EMR and EMT-level stand-by medical response at campus events and training members of the campus and community to provide life saving care through CPR and EMT courses.

name: Engineering Society
description_preview: An RSO for students interested in building things. Each quarter we host workshops, guest speakers, competitions, and projects, including rockets, electronics/robotics, and 3D printing, to give students fun ways to spend time and build engineering skills.

name: ENoK - Empowerment/Emancipation of North Koreans
description_preview: We are the only on-campus human rights advocacy group for North Korean defectors residing in the US. We provide 1-to-1 mentoring and tutoring services to these North Korean students, classes ranging from English, Music, to even Yoga.

name: Environmental Justice Task Force
description_preview: We are a student power organization committed to achieving social and ecological justice. We understand that this goal is deeply tied to questions of racial, economic, and gender justice, and is therefore a fundamentally political challenge.

name: Environmental Law Society
description_preview: ELS educates law students, as well as other members of the University of Chicago (UChicago) community and general public, about topics and careers in environmental law and works to promote sustainability at the Law School.

name: Environmental Research Group
description_preview: The Environmental Research Group is an undergraduate think tank devoted to interfacing science and social good to create sustainable change in Chicago through applicable, data-driven modeling, policy research and community outreach.

name: Equestria
description_preview: Equestria is an RSO that hosts horseback riding lessons off campus and is open to all members of the UChicago community. Riders of all ages and experience levels are welcome!

name: Ethics Bowl
description_preview: We teach, learn, and practice the procedures of competitive Ethics Bowl—including philosophical and ethical terminology, public speaking skills, deep and critical thinking for complex issues, and building strong arguments in collaboration with others.

name: Euphony Journal
description_preview: Euphony Journal is a biannual literary journal dedicated to publishing the finest work by current writers, both accomplished and aspiring.

name: EX Crew
description_preview: EX Crew is a competitive choreography group formed in 2009 with the hope of connecting with and enriching the dance community at UChicago, in Hyde Park, and in the city of Chicago. The crew performs and competes at various on-campus and Chicago events.

name: Federalist Society
description_preview: The Federalist Society is a group dedicated to freedom, the separation of governmental powers is central to our Constitution, and with the belief that it is the province and duty of the judiciary to say what the law is, not what is should be.

name: Fellowship of Christian Athletes
description_preview: FCA seeks to provide fellowship for Christians across the UChicago campus through the platform of sports and to invite others to engage in informal dialogue about Christ and the Gospel through weekly meetings and outreach events.

name: Feminist Forum
description_preview: Feminist Forum is a UChicago RSO dedicated to recentralizing feminist discussion on people of marginalized identities and groups. Our goal to uplift the voices of, and provide support for, BIPOC, LGBTQA+, and disabled people within this movement.

name: Fencing Club
description_preview: A club for both beginners and experienced fencers to practice, have fun, and compete in tournaments against other schools

name: Festival of the Arts
description_preview: Festival of the Arts, more dearly known as FOTA, has been a campus tradition since 1963. Throughout the year, FOTA hosts workshops, galleries, and various performance events in celebration of the talent, expression, and diversity of our student artists.

name: Field Hockey
description_preview: Recreational Field Hockey.

name: Figure Skating
description_preview: UChicago Figure Skating is a sports club that provides students the resources to maintain and advance their pre-existing skills. Members are welcome to join regular group skating sessions and volunteer for the neighbourhood Learn To Skate program.

name: Fire Escape Films
description_preview: Fire Escape Films is the University of Chicago's only organization for film production and education. Our members learn filmmaking as they participate in our productions, which are entirely written, directed, produced, and created by students.

name: Firebird Magazine
description_preview: Firebird Magazine is the University of Chicago’s premier student-run music publication. Our goal is to bring student-driven music journalism to campus, including interviews with student artists, album reviews, concert reviews, and music history pieces.

name: Folklore Society
description_preview: Founded in the 1950s, the UChicago Folklore Society is dedicated to celebrating folk music, dance, and arts on campus.  Our annual Folk Fest draws hundreds of people to Ida Noyes and Mandel Hall to enjoy concerts, jam sessions, workshops, and more!

name: Food Recovery Network
description_preview: Food Recovery Network is a service organization dedicated to addressing environmental justice and food insecurity by recovering leftover food on campus for local shelters and community centers.

name: Food Run Project
description_preview: Food Run Project provides food and resources to Chicago's homeless population. We see value in personal interaction with Chicago's poor, restoring dignity to a group often marginalized by mainstream society.

name: French Club
description_preview: A student organization that aims to promote the French language and Francophone cultures, unite Francophiles and Francophones, and stimulate discussion on social, political and cultural issues in the world.

name: Friends of Washington Park Youth Program
description_preview: Student Volunteers mentor and tutor children from the Washington Park neighborhoods. Done through academic enrichment packages and homework assistance.

name: Game Design
description_preview: UChicago Game Design is the on campus hub dedicated to creation and discussion of games, both digital and analogue.

name: Gargoyle Consulting Club
description_preview:
Gargoyle Consulting Club is a platform for PhDs, MDs, JDs, Master's, Post-docs, and Undergrads who are interested in a career in consulting. 
*** Please visit our website and subscribe to our listserv to stay informed of our resources and events.

name: Gateway to the Great Outdoors
description_preview: GGO (Gateway to the Great Outdoors) partners with low-income Chicago Public Schools to provide hands-on, inquiry-based environmental and outdoor education, nature-based outings and trips, and year-round mentorship to students.

name: GeneHackers
description_preview: The official UChicago iGEM team.

name: Geophysical Sciences Undergraduate Union
description_preview: GeoUnion is a forum for undergraduate students to engage with members of the geoscience community and other related fields. We hold regular presentations given by graduate students, post docs, faculty, and other visitors focused at an undergraduate level

name: German Club
description_preview: The University of Chicago German Club provides the entire UofC community with opportunities to engage with German language and culture, at any and all levels of proficiency and interest!

name: Go Club
description_preview: Go is an ancient and intellectually rewarding board game. Our club hosts weekly Go activities, including teaching games, guest lectures, off-campus tournaments, and outdoors events. We foster competition and camaraderie, offering challenges and joy.

name: Graduate Christian Fellowship
description_preview:
The Graduate Christian Fellowship (GCF) at UChicago is a community of
grad students cultivating the love of Jesus in the academy, city, and world.
Whatever your background, join us as we learn about Jesus together.

name: Grappling
description_preview: A platform for students and affiliates to train and compete in grappling martial arts (specifically Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu).

name: Groove Theory
description_preview: Groove Theory is a competitive collegiate dance crew dedicated to practicing street dance and spreading knowledge of hip hop culture. Come groove with us!

name: Guild of Change Ringers
description_preview: We ring the bells in the Reynolds club, and practice the ancient art of change ringing. New members are always welcome!

name: Gymnastics Club
description_preview: A club dedicated to practicing artistic gymnastics and introducing students to gymnastics skills.

name: Harris Community Action
description_preview: Harris Community Action (HCA) is a student organization at the Harris School of Public Policy that connects students to local community-based organizations to lead data and policy projects primarily during the Winter Quarter.

name: Health Professions Recruitment and Exposure Program
description_preview: HPREP members serve as mentors and friends to minority high school students. Area students travel to the University of Chicago campus to participate in a variety of lectures, discussions, and hands-on activities

name: Hellenic Student Association
description_preview: The Hellenic Student Association (HSA) brings students of both Hellenic and non-Hellenic backgrounds together in order to learn more about the culture, politics, and history of Greece. HSA will have social gatherings, discussions, and guest speakers.

name: High Fidelity Music Collective
description_preview: Welcome to our club, where high fidelity music enthusiasts and record collectors unite to delve into the rich tapestry of music history. We're more than just a gathering of audiophiles; we're a community that explores music through book clubs, unraveling

name: Hindu Sangam
description_preview: The Hindu Student Sangam creates a space for Hindu students to learn about and grow in their religious/spiritual practices, organizing weekly prayer sessions and other events for yearly festivals.

name: Hispanic and Luso-Brazilian Student Committee
description_preview: The Hispanic and Luso-Brazilian Student Committee (HBLSC) is a graduate student organization committed to the academic and intellectual development of the Spanish and Luso-Brazilian languages and literatures.

name: Hong Kong Student Association
description_preview: The Hong Kong Student Association aims to promote Hong Kong and its culture to all students at the University of Chicago through organizing cultural activities and study breaks.

name: HOPES 4 Foundations
description_preview: Through sustainable, direct consultations with Chicago principals & teachers, we strategically identify high-potential, overlooked students living in high-risk environments and support them for academic achievement across multiple years.

name: Ice Hockey (Men's)
description_preview: UChicago Men's Ice Hockey Team

name: Ice Hockey (Women's)
description_preview: We play various other university and recreational teams in the Chicagoland area and beyond; we are open to any interested university-affiliated women of all skill levels.

name: If/When/How: Lawyering for Reproductive Justice
description_preview: If/When/How: LRJ works to educate the community about reproductive justice issues and provides members with the tools necessary to advocate for reproductive justice and abortion access.

name: Indigenous Students Association
description_preview: We strive to foster a welcoming and united community of Indigenous people and allies from all corners of the globe. Through cultural gatherings and community engagement, we aim to uplift the voices of Indigenous peoples and create a safe space.

name: Indonesian Student Association at The University of Chicago
description_preview: We welcome everyone in University of Chicago community who has interest in Indonesia through our events and activities.

name: Institute of Politics
description_preview: The IOP aims to inspire and cultivate the next generation of political and public service leaders.

name: International Leadership Council
description_preview: The International Leadership Council, founded in 2003, is the University of Chicago's premier student business organization, founded to provide students with a platform to share knowledge and ideas across finance, entrepreneurship, and technology.

name: International Student Organization
description_preview: International Student Organization aims to build a supportive and inclusive community of international students at UChicago by organizing social and professional events.

name: Jade Chinese Music Ensemble
description_preview: Jade Chinese Music Ensemble

name: Japanese Student Association
description_preview: JSA serves all students interested in Japan and Japanese culture. We hope to raise awareness of Japanese culture, language, and current issues among the student body as well as the local community through a variety of activities and events.

name: Jewish Law Student Association
description_preview: To sponsor activities and events that improve the social and educational life of Jewish students at the Law School and the University.
JGrads Chabad at UChicago

name: Joint Research Safety Initiative
description_preview: The Joint Research Safety Initiative (JRSI) is a research safety community run by students that aims to provide centralized and accessible safety and educational resources for students and faculty. Our safety and  efficiency is up to us, and only us.

JOURNEES is a group of medical students interested in rural medicine and service learning. During academic breaks, students travel to rural underserved areas for clinical and community service experiences

name: Judo Club
description_preview: Dedicated to practicing judo ("gentle way", a Japanese martial art and Olympic sport) for competition, self-defense, good health, and camaraderie. No experience necessary!

name: Jugglers Enriching Lives Like Yours
description_preview: We are the official juggling and object manipulation club of the University of Chicago!

name: Kababayan
description_preview: We are a cultural and social RSO of the University of Chicago. Our mission is to provide an inclusive community for Filipinos, Filipino-Americans, and Southeast Asians at the University of Chicago.

name: Kappa Theta Pi
description_preview: Kappa Theta Pi is UChicago's first professional technology fraternity focused on five pillars: professional development, alumni connections, social growth, technological advancement, and academic support.

name: Kendo Club

name: Maroons for Israel
description_preview: Maroons for Israel

Previously known as M.E.Ch.A.

The Center for Leadership and Involvement's team of student advisors for RSOs.

We are Scav Hunt, as featured in The New Yorker, US News and World Report, The Guinness Book of World Records, and your dreams. 
For Scav info (boring) visit scavhunt.uchicago.edu.
For Scav lore (awesome) find an old scavvie and get them talking.

Spring 2024 New RSO

We are a group of seekers, dedicated to discovering and living by God's word in this modern age.

The Kidney Club at UChicago

Southside Free Clinic

description_preview: To play recreationally in a fun, low stress environment as well as to play competitively against other collegiate club golf teams across the nation.

description_preview: The Visuals Series serves as a space for Black beauty, euphoria, and excellence to be empowered and celebrated. By hosting quarterly photoshoots and community events, Visuals places creativity and collaboration at the forefront of the art making process.

name: UC Dancers

name: UChicago Bhangra

name: UChicago Biotechnology Association
description_preview: The mission of the UChicago Biotechnology Association (UCBA) is to provide resources and opportunities for career education and skill development to UChicago students and post-doctoral scholars.

name: UChicago Ceramics
description_preview: UChicago Ceramics offers interested individuals the opportunity to work with clay in a relaxed and informal environment. Instruction is mostly peer-to-peer and all skill levels are welcome.

description_preview: UChicago Effective Altruism aims to provide a space for effective altruists and intends to promote the ideas of effective altruism—the view that we should apply evidence to find the most high-impact ways to improve the world.

name: UChicago Energy & Climate Club
description_preview: The Energy & Climate Club is a community for undergraduate students interested in the energy and climate sectors. We seek to foster engagement through educational programming and pre-professional career opportunities!

name: UChicago Geographic Studies Club
description_preview: The University of Chicago Geographic Studies Club (UCGEO) is a general-interest RSO for undergraduate students to explore the world with weekly thematic meetings, field trips, guest speakers, and exciting events in the magnificent world of geography!

name: UChicago Harm Reduction Project
description_preview: UChicago Harm Reduction Project

name: UChicago Hillel
description_preview: UChicago Hillel is an organization for students on campus to form meaningful Jewish experiences for themselves. In doing so, we help facilitate an environment on campus that Jews and non-Jews alike want to be a part of.

name: UChicago International Development Society
description_preview: We are a group of undergrads with a keen interest in pursuing the up-and-coming field of international development. We hope to increase students’ awareness about this field’s insights and the exciting career opportunities it offers.

name: UChicago Kehillah
description_preview: UChicago Kehillah

name: UChicago MannMukti
description_preview: Our goal is to tackle the stigma surrounding mental health in the South Asian community on campus and beyond through open dialogue, advocacy, workshops, and community outreach.

name: UChicago Maya Dance Company
description_preview: UChicago Maya Dance Company is a fusion dance group dedicated to innovative, demanding, and exploratory choreography and performance. We draw influence from styles such as contemporary, jazz, and hip-hop.

name: UChicago Plus
description_preview: UChicago＋ is a social RSO focused on connecting LGBT+ undergraduate and graduate students from all schools across campus. Regular events include coffee meet-ups, weekly board game night and grad student pub night. Everyone is welcome to join!

name: UChicago Private Equity Club
description_preview: UChicago Private Equity is a student organization that focuses on educating its members on private equity industry knowledge and skills as well as helping members achieve their career goals.

name: UChicago Quantum Society
description_preview: The UChicago Quantum Society is a group of students exploring quantum computing and quantum science, from high-temperature superconductors to quantum compilers.

name: UChicago Quest+
description_preview: This organization seeks to serve as a support network for Quest Scholars, Odyssey Scholars and all First-generation, Low-income students at UChicago. We provide mentoring, networking, and leadership opportunities for our members.

name: UChicago Robotics
description_preview: UChicago Robotics is an engineering community dedicated to empowering students in the field of robotics. We offer education in mechanical engineering and programming with applications to robotics competitions, research projects, and community service.

name: UChicago Smash
description_preview: We are the student-run Super Smash Bros. scene at the University of Chicago! Participate in weekly tournaments, compete for a spot on the UChicago Power Rankings, travel to tournaments, and make friends both at the University and throughout Chicago.

name: UChicago Synapse
description_preview: UChicago Synapse is an organization dedicated to supporting those whose lives have been affected in some way by traumatic and acquired brain injury through such things as peer support groups, buddy programs, and special events.

name: UChicago Transit Enthusiasts & Explorers
description_preview: Come use your U-Pass Ventra card with us! We are an organization dedicated to promoting transit use in Chicago and beyond through social excursions in the city, educational series, and direct advocacy. Planes, trains, bikes, buses... you name it!

name: UChicago Triathlon Club
description_preview: The triathlon community encourages multi-sport engagement at UofC, providing both a competitive and recreational support system. We are an active community with a wide range of experience levels. We support members competing locally and nationally.

name: UChicago UNICEF
description_preview: UChicago UNICEF is a club that is dedicated to supporting children throughout the world in ways such as child protection, survival, education, and female empowerment.

name: UChicago Vietnamese Student Association
description_preview: The Vietnamese Student Association at the University of Chicago facilitates Vietnamese cultural exploration and engagement through festive/informational events, arts, and cuisine appreciation. We welcome everyone with an interest in Vietnamese culture.

name: UChicagOrigami
description_preview: Welcome to UChicagOrigami, where we promote and enjoy the art of paper-folding.

name: UChicomics
description_preview: This RSO provides a community for UChicago students to read, discuss, create, and fund comics, illustrations, and other 2D visual art. Activities include tabling at local conventions, reading and talking about comics/illustrations, and field trips.

name: Ultimate Frisbee (Women and Non-Binary)
description_preview: Ultimate Frisbee: a fun, fast-paced, team-oriented sport.  All skill-levels welcome!

name: Undergraduate Investment Banking Group
description_preview: UIBG provides students with educational seminars specific to investment banking, and hosts case competitions, guest speakers, and networking opportunities with top investment banks and alumni in order to prepare students for the recruitment process.

name: Undergraduate Philosophy Club
description_preview: The Philosophy Club provides a forum for the exploration of philosophical ideas outside of the classroom. We especially aim to showcase undergraduate work through student presentations of their own papers. We welcome anyone to join the discussion.

name: Undergraduate Student Government
description_preview: Undergraduate Student Government's (USG) mission is represent the University of Chicago undergraduate population, address student concerns, and create positive changes in the broader collegiate, University, and Chicago communities.

name: United Against Inequities in Disease
description_preview: UAID is dedicated to combating health inequities in neighboring communities through partnerships with local non-profits, and raising awareness on campus through speaker events, discussions and more.

name: University Ballet of Chicago
description_preview: UBallet seeks to promote a love of ballet and provide opportunities for technical training through free weekly classes, open to members of the University and Hyde Park community; as well as putting on two full-length ballet performances a year.

name: University Community Service Center
description_preview: UCSC's goal is to support students in becoming productive, thoughtful citizens and effective, inspiring leaders in their communities and professions.

name: University Ministry of Christ Church Chicago
description_preview: The University Ministry of Christ Church Chicago comes alongside students (grad and undergrad) as they pursue their academic goals. Together, we live out our Christian faith through building community and meeting regularly to study the Bible together.

name: University of Chicago Association of Peruvian Students
description_preview: University of Chicago Association of Peruvian Students - UCAPS. We connect, organize and boost our community. Por y para el Perú 🇵🇪

name: University of Chicago College Democrats
description_preview: UC Dems welcomes all political persuasions to our meetings, discussions, and events, and hope to provide great politics-focused opportunities on campus! Meetings weekly, Tuesdays at 7PM in Bartlett Lounge.

name: University of Chicago Japanese Animation Society
description_preview: The Japanese Animation Society works to promote the appreciation of anime on campus and provide spaces in which students can enjoy and express their love for anime.

name: University of Chicago Ki-Aikido Club
description_preview: The UChicago Ki-Aikido Club trains in the dynamic martial art of Shin Shin Tōitsu Aikidō (Ki-Aikidō). All are welcome; no prior experience is necessary.

name: University of Chicago Political Union
description_preview: A non-partisan forum for political discourse on salient issues in the world and on campus.

name: University of Chicago Southeast Asia Society
description_preview: Increasing Southeast Asian Perspectives on Campus

name: University of Chicago Undergraduate Law Magazine
description_preview: The UChicago Undergraduate Law Magazine is the College's only undergraduate publication focused on academic legal writing. In addition to publishing annual print editions and social media content, we will host educational workshops and film screenings.

name: University Theater
description_preview: University Theater is the premier student theater RSO at UChicago, producing over 35 annual shows that range from staged readings to mainstage productions. We provide opportunities to act in, direct, manage, and design shows - no experience required!

name: Urban Policy Student Association
description_preview: UPSA is a community of students interested in the policy decisions, political dynamics, and social issues that shape cities around the world.

name: URoad Runners

name: UROCK Climbing Club

name: Veteran Scholar Association
description_preview: VSA is the UChicago chapter of Student Veterans of America. We have a commitment to recognize, support, and mentor military-affiliated students through networking opportunities, resource awareness, and campus and community engagement.

name: Voices in Your Head
description_preview: Voices in Your Head (also known as Voices) is an all gender acappella group comprised of both graduate and undergraduate students. They perform music from a wide variety of genres, and are known for their unique interpretations and arrangements.

name: Volleyball
description_preview: In the absence of a Men's Varsity team, Volleyball provides men and women a place to play volleyball at a fairly competitive level. That being said, everyone is welcome, and we will try to improve everyone's ability with drills, games, and tournaments.

name: Vélo Club
description_preview: UCVC is a major club structure for the cycling community in Hyde Park. We will host weekly group rides focusing on cycling techniques. We welcome anyone who is interested in either recreational riding or racing.

name: Water Polo
description_preview: A coed water polo club team that competes year-round.

name: WHPK
description_preview: "The Pride of the South Side." Broadcasting 100% independent programming live daily to the South Side of Chicago and streaming worldwide at www.whpk.org

name: Windmill Chinese Drama Club

name: Women and Youth Supporting Each Other

name: Women in Business
description_preview: University of Chicago Women in Business (UCWiB) is dedicated to advancing the success of enterprising young women entering the corporate world. WiB unites and teaches undergraduate female leaders, equipping them with the knowledge and skills to succeed.
Women in Economics strives to create a community for aspiring female economists that will provide support in research endeavors, resources through external connections, and mentorship opportunities.

name: Women in Science
description_preview: Women in Science's mission is to bring together women at all levels of science, enhancing their educational and professional experiences and providing a forum for discussion of the issues they face.

name: Women Who Lift
description_preview: A strong and supportive community with a passion for weightlifting and women's empowerment.

name: Women's Squash
description_preview: Women's Squash Sports Club

name: Women+ in Chemistry
description_preview: Graduate student/post-doc-focused organization that aims to foster relationships between women and gender-minorities ("women+") in the University of Chicago’s Department of Chemistry through social and professional development events.

name: Women+ in Law
description_preview: University of Chicago Women+ in Law is dedicated to providing a space for women and nonbinary students at UChicago to explore careers in law, navigate graduate school admissions, and form a community among other students interested in law.

name: Writers' Workshop
description_preview: Organized creative writing workshops.

name: Yoga Club
description_preview: We are a student organisation which runs drop-in yoga classes two to three times a week.
